The governments of the Netherlands nationalize a part of the Fortis Bank.
The States of the Netherlands - being the first in Europe - will help with a nationalization of the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis that is in trouble due to the effect of the mortgage crisis of the North American market: the three countries will support in total with 11.2 billion euros to this financial and insurance institution that also has businesses in Hungary.
This weekend the governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands held high-level consultations with the president of the European Central Bank and the head of economic competition at the European Commission.
The Fortis Bank is the first to suffer the crisis of the euro area in the framework of the international financial crisis that has been occurring in several waves more than a year ago, therefore the decisions taken with respect to the Bank, in a sense can be considered as precedent.
According to the decision taken early Sunday, the three states will buy about half (49 percent) of the property owned by the Bank in their area.
The Bank will surely sell a part of its business, including mainly the activities -mainly insurance- bought last year from the Dutch ABN Amró.
Fortis stocks started a sharp decline last week and by the second half of the week there were already significant signs of crisis at the institution.
However, analysts agree that with its 85,000 employees this Bank is too large to allow it to fail.
Shares of the company fell 12 percent on Friday alone, the lowest point in 14 years.
Since January the value of the shares has declined by more than two-thirds.
Looking at current stock prices, the total value of the group’s capital in the market is around 14 billion euros, but according to the company’s executives this is not real.
The Bank’s management blamed the sharp decline in Fortis shares on US market insecurities in connection with the approval of the US $700 billion package plan.
On Monday, stocks showed a slight increase.
On Friday, Filip Dierckx was appointed as the bank’s new CEO.
The Bank also looked for private investors, but so far no one has given a concrete offer.
The Belgian government had previously assured investors that they had nothing to worry about, they would not lose their money.
Among the Bank’s clients so far there was no panic, they did not invade the bank offices to withdraw their money.
El Fortis has its own branch in Hungary and has also bought leasing companies.
Fox in the chicken coop
In the United States, life and health insurance companies often refuse to sign an insurance contract when they see drug purchase data.
Privacy policy specialists fear that the market for personal data will become uncontrollable.
"There are personal data protection programs, which link the use of prescription data in all cases to the approval of the given person.
It must be in independent hands, because if not, "we trust the chicken coop to the fox" - quotes the Washington Post Richard Dick, designer of the program to track prescriptions.
Insurance companies make the insurance price and indemnity amount depend on the client’s health status and if they believe the risk is excessive, they simply don’t make the contract.
Before, they sent the client to medical control and signed the contract with him knowing the result of the control.
Ten years ago Dick invented a much cheaper procedure: with the customer identification number he easily gets from pharmacies the list of drugs purchased in the last year and a half and the program itself draws the conclusion about the diseases and state of health of the customer.
For example, if you consistently take large doses of cholesterol-lowering pills, it indicates that the level of fat in your blood is virtually incurably high, thus you are immediately placed in a higher risk category.
Numerous versions of the program circulate, some even establish a number of risks, so that the insurance company in addition to the administration hardly has anything to do, although there are small difficulties in this regard.
Among the disadvantages of the program is for example that some medicines are multipurpose, for example certain substances serve both to treat headache and for heat waves and even as antidepressants.
The latter is a major risk-increasing factor for insurance companies while the former do not.
Special companies were set up to consult and process these data, which, before acquiring the necessary information from pharmacies, ask for the patient’s approval.
The authorities already force them to this, although they were not fined for negligence until now.
Some companies have recently also developed laboratory test results and linked them with drug consumption data to obtain more accurate information about the patient’s health status.
More and more companies have access to this data and simultaneously it is increasingly difficult to control its use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those who provide health services.
The bill that gives the right to control the specialized companies for the provision of personal data is already before Congress.
Dick Richard acknowledges that this is insufficient: he therefore developed his program, which will require the person’s specific approval for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another matter that such a person cannot deny his approval, because otherwise the insurance companies will not sign the contract with him.
So the hens, in spite of everything, are exposed to the good will of the fox.
